{
  "stem": "1550.3",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were under guard by the local police.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the-- the-- the sergeant and the-- and the upper-- upper echelon, so to speak, were all British.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So the-- the camp commandant [INAUDIBLE] the certain captain armitage was a British police captain.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there were several police sergeants that had accompanied us from Palestine and who stayed there for four years, actually.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were two police-- two or three police sergeants from the Palestine police-- British Palestine police-- who stayed with us in Mauritius.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were treated like internees.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Let's say it this way.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had complete freedom inside the camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Nobody bothered us inside the camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were not allowed to go out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We had-- you know, we could send as many letters as we wished and-- and so forth.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We had our own kitchens and our own cultural activities.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can't go into this a little bit more in greater detail, of course.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Right?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It took some time to get-- get organized.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we arrived first, it was-- first of all, in the first instance everybody was very depressing because what was the future going to be?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We are in this camp on this-- on this godforsaken island.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There are no Jews, by the way.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not one Jew living in Mauritius.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Not one.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Most of the population is black-- is-- is Creole.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The-- the-- the language of the country is a kind of a Creole French, because at one time, Mauritius was French until Napoleon lost the war, and then it became a British colony.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, at that time-- at that-- and now it's an independent state, but at the time it was a British colony.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were also many Indians living there.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
